[['Shine 100 vs splendor please'], ['Koppppp'], ['ğŸ˜Šul'], ['S1 Pro vs Activa 25km/day for yrs 10 yrs. 
Ola (with battery replacement) = Rs. 3,01,099
Activa = Rs. 6,03,979
i.e. huge diff of Rs. 3,02,880

Below is the breakdown of the cost of ownership. I made following 2 assumptions:
1. Assuming the battery needs to be replaced after 5 years which is not true. The battery will easily last 10 years with reduced range. 
2. Considered 100%  avg. elect. price inflation i.e. Rs. 20/kWh for the highest slab in Maharashtra for 10 years compared to the current rate (Rs. 10/kWh), whereas for petrol 70% price hike for 10 years (current is Rs. 106/ltr)


S1 Pro: 
On-road Cost Ola S1 = Rs 1,50,399 (incl. Extended warranty, helmets, accessories)
Average electricity cost for 10 years = Rs 20/kWh
Battery = 3.97 kWh
Cost per charge = 20 x 3.97 = Rs. 79.4
10 years average mileage of S1 = 110 KM/charge 
Cost per KM = 79.4 % 110 = Rs. 0.72/km
Price per 25 KM = 25 x 0.72 = Rs 18
10 years cost of running = 18 x 365 x 10 = Rs. 65,700
10-year approx maintenance cost (OLA Care Plus) = 3500 x 10 = 35,000
Battery cost after 5 years = Rs. 50000 (Battery will literally last for 10+ years. )  
Ownership cost = 1,50,399 + 65,700 + 35,000 + 50,000 = Rs. 3,01,099

Activa 125 H-Smart:
On-road price in my city = Rs. 1,17,729 
Average estimated price of petrol for 10 years = Rs. 150
Average 10 years mileage = 30km/ltr.
Cost per KM = 150 % 30  = Rs 5/km
Daily running = 25KM
10 years cost of running = 5 x 25 x 365 x 10 = Rs. 4,56,250
10  year approx maintenance cost = 3000 x 10 = 30000
Ownership cost = 1,17,729 + 4,56,250 + 30,000 = Rs. 6,03,979'], ['Super meteor 650 vs Bajaj Avenger 220 vs RE classic 350 reborn'], ['A buyer's perspective here.. It is this uncertainty and fear that people will not have with a scooter like Activa (or any other ICE scooter for that matter). For safety's sake, it is easier to choose the "safer" option which is Activa.
